ure data validation prevents corruption at input boundaries\n\n## Encryption (§164.312(a)(2)(iv))\n- Verify PHI at rest is encrypted using AES-256 or equivalent\n- Check that encryption keys are managed separately from encrypted data\n- Ensure key rotation policies are implemented and automated\n- Validate that PHI in backups and archives is also encrypted\n\n## Business Associate Requirements\n- Identify all third-party services that may process PHI\n- Verify BAA (Business Associate Agreement) requirements for each\n- Check that PHI is not sent to analytics, logging, or monitoring services without BAA\n\nFor each finding, provide:\n1. **HIPAA reference** (e.g., §164.312(a)(1) — Access Control)\n2. **Risk level** (Critical / High / Medium / Low)\n3. **Finding** — what the current implementation does\n4. **Requirement** — what HIPAA mandates\n5. **Remediation** — specific technical changes with code examples where applicable",
