on procedures\n- **SC-13 Cryptographic Protection**: Ensure FIPS 140-2 validated encryption for data at rest and in transit\n- **SC-28 Protection of Information at Rest**: Verify all sensitive data encrypted at rest with separate key management\n\n## Configuration Management (CM Family)\n- **CM-2 Baseline Configuration**: Verify documented and enforced baseline configurations for all system components\n- **CM-6 Configuration Settings**: Check that security-relevant settings follow hardening benchmarks (CIS, DISA STIGs)\n- **CM-7 Least Functionality**: Verify unnecessary ports, services, and protocols are disabled\n- **CM-8 Information System Component Inventory**: Ensure complete, accurate, and current inventory of all system components\n\n## Incident Response (IR Family)\n- **IR-4 Incident Handling**: Verify documented incident response procedures with defined roles and escalation paths\n- **IR-6 Incident Reporting**: Check US-CERT reporting capabilities within required timeframes\n\n## Risk Assessment (RA Family)\n- **RA-5 Vulnerability Scanning**: Verify automated vulnerability scanning (DAST, SAST, dependency scanning) in CI/CD pipeline\n\nFor each control assessment, provide:\n1. **Control ID** (e.g., AC-2, AU-3, SC-8)\n2. **Control title and family**\n3. **Implementation status**: Implemented / Partially Implemented / Planned / Not Implemented\n4. **Evidence** — what exists in the codebase/configuration\n5. **Gap analysis** — what is missing or insufficient\n6. **Remediation plan** — ordered technical steps to achieve compliance\n7. **FedRAMP impact level relevance** (Low / Moderate / High)",
