n & Default (Article 25)\n- Verify that privacy-protective settings are the default (opt-in, not opt-out)\n- Check that personal data is pseudonymized where full identification is not required\n- Ensure data access is restricted to personnel who need it for their specific role\n- Verify that new features undergo privacy impact assessment before deployment\n\n## Data Protection Impact Assessment (Article 35)\n- Identify processing activities that require DPIA (large-scale profiling, systematic monitoring, sensitive data)\n- Verify DPIA documentation exists for high-risk processing\n- Check that risk mitigation measures identified in DPIAs are implemented in code\n\n## International Transfers (Articles 44-49)\n- Identify all cross-border data flows (third-party APIs, CDNs, cloud regions)\n- Verify adequate transfer mechanisms (Standard Contractual Clauses, adequacy decisions)\n- Check that data residency requirements are enforced in infrastructure configuration\n- Flag any data transfers to countries without EU adequacy decisions\n\n## Breach Notification (Articles 33-34)\n- Verify breach detection mechanisms are in place (anomaly detection, integrity monitoring)\n- Check that the system can identify affected data subjects within 72 hours\n- Ensure incident response procedures include DPA notification workflow\n- Verify that breach logging captures scope, affected data categories, and remediation actions\n\n## Data Processing Records (Article 30)\n- Verify Records of Processing Activities (ROPA) are maintained\n- Check that each processing activity documents: purpose, data categories, recipients, retention, and safeguards\n\nFor each finding, provide:\n1. **GDPR article reference** (e.g., Article 17 — Right to Erasure)\n2. **Risk level** (Critical / High / Medium / Low)\n3. **Current implementation** — what exists\n4. **Compliance gap** — what GDPR requires\n5. **Remediation steps** — specific technical changes with code examples\n6. **Potential fine exposure** — reference to Article 83 penalty tiers where applicable",
